<h1 style="margin-bottom:0px;">Application load balancer</h1><div class="f14 metric" style="color:#656668;display:flex;"><img src="/assets/images/calendar.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="updateDate">&nbsp; Updated on 26/06/2019</span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img src="/assets/images/updated.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="readTime">&nbsp; 2 minutes to read</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><br><div class="mw-parser-output"><p>&nbsp;AWS Application Load Balancer is used to serve end users to access SMA suite from web browsers. 
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Create_Application_Load_Balancer">Create Application Load Balancer</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/AppLoaBalOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=1" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Create Application Load Balancer">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/AppLoaBalOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Create Application Load Balancer">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<ol><li>Click <b>Create Load Balancer</b> from AWS console <a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://console.aws.amazon.com/ec2/v2/home#LoadBalancers">https://console.aws.amazon.com/ec2/v2/home#LoadBalancers</a></li>
<li>Select <b>Application Load Balancer</b> and click <b>Create</b>.</li>
<li>Complete <b>Step 1 Configure Load Balancer</b>:
<ul><li>In the <b>Basic Configuration</b> section, select <b>internet-facing</b> for <b>Scheme</b>.</li>
<li>In the <b>Listeners</b> section,  add listeners for the 3 Target Groups  with <b>Protocol</b> HTTPSP and <b>Ports</b> 443, 3000, and 5443 respectively.</li>
<li>In the <b>Availability Zones</b> section, associate the 3 Availability Zones, with their public subnet selected. <a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsBridge2019.02ALB4.jpg" src="/mediawiki/images/b/b6/OpsBridge2019.02ALB4.jpg" width="1011" height="313" data-file-width="1011" data-file-height="313"></a></li></ul></li>
<li>Complete <b>Step 2 Configure Security Settings</b>.
<ul><li>Upload or create a certificate that will be used by <b>Application Load Balancer</b> to handle HTTPS access from end users' web browsers. You can select <b>AWS Certificate Manager</b> recommended by AWS. <a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/acm/latest/userguide/acm-overview.html">https://docs.aws.amazon.com/acm/latest/userguide/acm-overview.html</a> <a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsBridge2019.02ALB5.jpg" src="/mediawiki/images/1/16/OpsBridge2019.02ALB5.jpg" width="821" height="456" data-file-width="821" data-file-height="456"></a></li>
<li>Configure <b>Security Group</b> for Application Load Balancer with inbound rules shown below: <a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsBridge2019.02ALB6.jpg" src="/mediawiki/images/f/f1/OpsBridge2019.02ALB6.jpg" width="737" height="222" data-file-width="737" data-file-height="222"></a></li></ul></li></ol>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Configure_Application_Load_Balancer">Configure Application Load Balancer</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/AppLoaBalOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=2" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Configure Application Load Balancer">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/AppLoaBalOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Configure Application Load Balancer">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<ol><li>After <b>Application Load Balancer</b> was created successfully, configure the load balancer Listeners to associate with the right HTTPS Target Groups. <a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsBridge2019.02ALB8.jpg" src="/mediawiki/images/4/45/OpsBridge2019.02ALB8.jpg" width="938" height="430" data-file-width="938" data-file-height="430"></a>You may disable listeners <b>3000</b> and <b>5443</b> after the suite installation.</li>
<li>Update the idle timeout value to suit the Service Management Automation applications. You need to set the Application Load Balancer's <b>Idle timeout</b> value to at least <b>180</b> seconds. This setting is under the Description tab, in the Attributes section.   <a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itom/File:ALB_Timeout.png" target="1" rel="nofollow"><img alt="ALB Timeout.png" src="/mediawiki/images/9/95/ALB_Timeout.png" width="947" height="284" data-file-width="947" data-file-height="284"></a><div class="Admonition_Note"><span class="autonumber">Note </span>If you experience common <b>Application Load Balancer</b> problems, refer to the following AWS document: <a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/elasticloadbalancing/latest/application/introduction.html">https://docs.aws.amazon.com/elasticloadbalancing/latest/application/introduction.html</a> </div></li></ol>

